<subSubSection pageId="31" pageNumber="30" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="31.[191,1441,289,554]" pageId="31" pageNumber="30">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,363,289,315]" pageId="31" pageNumber="30">Redescription.</emphasis>
<emphasis box="[372,415,290,316]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="30">Size</emphasis>
. Length 7.0 mm; width 
<quantity box="[700,792,290,316]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.8" pageId="31" pageNumber="30" unit="mm" value="1.8">1.8 mm</quantity>
. 
<emphasis box="[805,864,290,315]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="30">Form</emphasis>
. As in 
<figureCitation box="[951,1046,290,316]" captionStart="Figures 106–109" captionStartId="67.[192,279,1859,1885]" captionTargetBox="[192,1436,213,1828]" captionTargetId="figure-10@67.[192,1440,213,1828]" captionTargetPageId="67" captionText="Figures 106–109. Habitus of Axina species. 106) Axina polycaula. 107) A. proxima. 108) A.rio. 109) A. villa." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4565031" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4565031/files/figure.png" pageId="31" pageNumber="30">Fig. 107</figureCitation>
. 
<emphasis box="[1059,1120,290,316]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="30">Color</emphasis>
. Forebody dark castaneous; antenna testaceous; pterothorax, legs, and abdomen testaceous; elytra bicolorous, mostly testaceous in basal 1/3 and totally testaceous in distal third; basal 1/3 with oblique brown line at middle that begins at elytral basal margin, oblong brown macula behind elytron middle. 
<emphasis box="[698,757,391,417]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="30">Head</emphasis>
. Cranium finely punctate, frons wider than length of antennal pedicel; EW/FW 30/15. 
<emphasis box="[457,535,425,451]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="30">Thorax</emphasis>
. Pronotum finely punctate, with 2 tumescences, concave at middle; PW/PL 70/95; elytra with substriate asetiferous punctures extend backwards slightly beyond elytral middle; EL/EW 310/60. 
<emphasis box="[192,298,493,519]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="30">Abdomen</emphasis>
. Aedeagus (
<figureCitation box="[437,519,493,520]" captionStart="Figures 50–55" captionStartId="51.[192,279,978,1004]" captionTargetBox="[320,1271,213,948]" captionTargetId="figure-10@51.[320,1271,213,948]" captionText="Figures 50–55. Aedeagi. 5) Axina basalis. 51) A. lateralis. 52) A. munda. 53) A. phallospina. 54) A. proxima. 55) A. trinalis." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4586063" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4586063/files/figure.png" pageId="31" pageNumber="30">Fig. 54</figureCitation>
), phallobasic lobes short, inner margin with spine; outer margin of phallic plates minutely serrate; phallobasic apodeme abbreviated.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="31.[192,1440,569,629]" pageId="31" pageNumber="30">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,310,569,595]" pageId="31" pageNumber="30">Variation.</emphasis>
<emphasis box="[322,365,570,596]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="30">Size</emphasis>
. Length 5.5–9.0 mm; width 
<quantity box="[711,854,569,596]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.9" metricValueMax="2.5" metricValueMin="1.3" pageId="31" pageNumber="30" unit="mm" value="1.9" valueMax="2.5" valueMin="1.3">1.3–2.5 mm</quantity>
. The brown markings on the elytral disc vary in prominence.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="31.[192,1440,645,706]" pageId="31" pageNumber="30">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,377,645,671]" pageId="31" pageNumber="30">Natural history.</emphasis>
Specimens were collected in 
<collectingCountry box="[704,769,645,671]" name="Brazil" pageId="31" pageNumber="30">Brazil</collectingCountry>
during March, September, November, and December, some at 
<specimenCount box="[219,295,679,706]" pageId="31" pageNumber="30" type="generic">
<quantity box="[219,292,679,706]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.0" pageId="31" pageNumber="30" unit="m" value="800.0">800 m</quantity>
.
</specimenCount>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
